Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place the @demi garlic baguettes{2} onto one side of a lined #baking tray{}.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto the other side of the tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @creme fraiche{150%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{250%ml} for the sauce to a #saucepan{}.

Heat on high and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Stir in the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g}. Simmer, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Next, stir in the @fresh pesto{32%g}, @baby spinach{40%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir a knob of @?butter{knob} into the pasta.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Serve the pasta in #bowls{} topped with the salmon. Sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Slice and serve the garlic bread alongside. Enjoy!

> Deliciously easy to cook, it only takes 3 steps to put this Easy Salmon on Fresh Pesto Tagliatelle on the table. Combine our chef-approved shortcuts and simple instructions to make a restaurant quality dinner that's as easy as 1-2-3!